Manage the KVM virtual machines with virsh
last update: 2013-09-26
Paul Stivers

A short list of important commands

	virsh --connect qemu:///system  # connect to the virtual shell
	
		help # lists the options for virsh
		
		list --all # show all VMs, running and inactive
		
		list # show all running VMs
		
		start vm1 
		
		shutdown vm1 # graceful shutdown
		
		destroy vm1 # Immediately stop. Like pulling the power plug
		
		undefine vm1 # completely remove the VM.
		
		suspend vm1
		
		resume vm1
		
		quit # to exit virsh
		
--
end
	

